'One mode of the divine teaching is the incarnation of the spirit in a form,—in forms, like my own.',
'I live in society, with persons who answer to thoughts in my own mind, or express a certain obedience to the great instincts to which I live.',
'I see its presence to them.',
'I am certified of a common nature; and these other souls, these separated selves, draw me as nothing else can.',
