'A man who is not happy in the company cannot find any word in his memory that will fit the occasion.',
'All his information is a little impertinent.',
'A man who is happy there, finds in every turn of the conversation equally lucky occasions for the introduction of that which he has to say.',
'The favorites of society, and what it calls whole souls, are able men and of more spirit than wit, who have no uncomfortable egotism, but who exactly fill the hour and the company;',
