'The epitaph of Sir Jenkin Grout is not wholly unintelligible to the present age:',
'“Here lies Sir Jenkin Grout, who loved his friend and persuaded his enemy:',
'what his mouth ate, his hand paid for:',
'what his servants robbed, he restored:',
'if a woman gave him pleasure, he supported her in pain:',
'he never forgot his children;',
'and whoso touched his finger, drew after it his whole body.”',
'Even the line of heroes is not utterly extinct.',
'There is still ever some admirable person in plain clothes, standing on the wharf, who jumps in to rescue a drowning man;',
